Crioprosopus is a genus of long-horned beetles in the family Cerambycidae. There are about 13 described species in Crioprosopus.The genus Callona was determined to be a synonym of Crioprosopus in 2015, and the species C. championi, C. iridescens, C. thoracicus, C. rimosus, C. thoracicus, and C. tricolor were moved from Callona to Crioprosopus.